    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Implements that use a reservoir of ink to make a mark or marks. A marker may have pointed or blunt tips, usually of fiber. It is distiguished from a felt-tip pen in that it typically makes a thicker mark than a pen and is more often used for labeling or marking rather than writing or drawing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000000651/ADAG, Glossary for Technique, Medium, and Support (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pennen die uitwisbare gekleurde inkt bevatten en een verscheidenheid van puntige of stompe punten gemaakt van vilt, nylon of vezels.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>可利用儲墨槽來繪製標記的工具。麥克筆的筆尖包含尖頭型或鈍頭型，通常是以纖維製成。麥克筆與簽字筆不同，其標記效果較一般的筆來得粗，因此較常用於繪製標誌或標記符號，而非用於書寫或繪圖。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
